Looking at the name and the statement: how about
```suggestion
theorem ne_zero_iff_exists_coeff_ne_zero_and_weight
    (f : MvPowerSeries σ R):
    f ≠ 0 ↔ (∃ n : ℕ, ∃ d : σ →₀ ℕ, coeff R d f ≠ 0 ∧ weight w d = n) := by
```

```suggestion
theorem coeff_eq_zero_of_lt_weightedOrder {d : σ →₀ ℕ} (h : ↑(weight w d) < f.weightedOrder w) :
```

```suggestion
theorem min_le_weightedOrder_add (f g : MvPowerSeries σ R) :
```
or maybe
```suggestion
theorem min_weightedOrder_le_add (f g : MvPowerSeries σ R) :
```
I chose the second suggestion.

As with the comment on the other PR: please state the name with `le`
```suggestion
theorem add_weightedOrder_le_weightedOrder_mul [DecidableEq σ] (f g : MvPowerSeries σ R) :
```
or
```suggestion
theorem le_weightedOrder_mul [DecidableEq σ] (f g : MvPowerSeries σ R) :
```
The current name could be an alias.
I chose the second one.
Also : I added the initial name as an alias, and did a similar modification for the already existing `PowerSeries.order_mul_ge`
See comment above.
See comment above.
Should this be called `min_order_le_add`?
It looks like it is a typo, it was `HahnSeries.min_order_le_order_add`
OK, I will restore it, thanks!
I guess this can move close to the def'n of weight?
I move this theorem to the one that defines `Finsupp.weight`. (That forces me to add an `import`, though.)
Idem?
Yes.
Please qualify `instNoZeroDivisors`
done. Anyway, this instance only appears in another PR. (I messed up the docstrings)
The double dash looks a little off here. I suggest you match the list above
Do you want to also add the `f = 0` version? (Then this one could probably be `by simpa using f.eq_zero_….not`
added. It is just "ext_iff".
When renaming results, please add the deprecated alias

```suggestion
(For example: the homogeneous components of degree 1 of the multivariate power
```
Space before colon in code, but note that this is also in `variable` above
Add the `eq_zero` variant?
I don't think this is needed anymore
indeed.
I think we prefer coercion of bare up-arrows

```suggestion
  by_contra! H
```
Why do you need `erw`?
because `rw` doesn't work, even if I provide all arguments I can think of.

On the other hand, I noticed that `ne_top_iff_exists` furnishes something in `WithTop Nat`, while `weightedOrder_eq_nat` expected something in `Nat\infty`, so specifying the type of `hn`on line 250 was enough to have `rw` work.

```suggestion
theorem eq_zero_iff_forall_coeff_zero {f : MvPowerSeries σ R} :
```
It seems the current standard.
It's probably better to update the date here.
`f` can be implicit here (and in various iff lemmas below).

```suggestion
    f ≠ 0 ↔ (f.weightedOrder w).toNat = f.weightedOrder w := by
```
You can do the same in various places below.

```suggestion
theorem coeff_eq_zero_of_lt_weightedOrder {d : σ →₀ ℕ} (h : weight w d < f.weightedOrder w) :
```
